The investor entrusted his money to one Management Company. Time passed, he decided to ask. Client: how are we doing? Manager: “The working conditions were terrible, but we managed. The stock market could have sold us twice and thrice to zero and we could have lost everything more than once, but we came out brilliantly losing all your money in one go. It could have been worse. In other words, you don't owe us anything. We to you too. Thank you for your cooperation. It was such a pleasure to work with you. We are waiting for you again.”